16/03/2003
TIRANA, Albania -- Meeting Friday (14 March) with the OSCE's representative in Tirana, President Alfred Moisiu said resolving property issues and electoral reform remain the priorities of state policy.
Also Friday, parties in parliament opened a round-table discussion on electoral reform and constitutional amendments.
The talks were initiated by Sali Berisha, the leader of the opposition Democratic Party.
Earlier, eight opposition parties adopted a joint statement, opting for a proportional electoral system.
(ATA - 14/03/03)
